is a train station on the [[Ensh&lt;U+016B&gt; Railway Line] ]in Hamakita-ku, Hamamatsu, Shizuoka Prefecture, Japan
Station History
Ensh&lt;U+016B&gt;-Kobayashi Station was established on December 6, 1909 as . It was given its present name in April 1923. The station has been unmanned since 1974. The station building was rebuilt in 1982.
Lines
Ensh&lt;U+016B&gt; Railway
Ensh&lt;U+016B&gt; Railway Line
Layout
Ensh&lt;U+016B&gt;-Kobayashi Station is an unmanned station with a single island platform, with the station building built onto one end of the platform. The station building has automated ticket machines, and automated turnstiles which accept the NicePass smart card, as well as ET Card, a magnetic card ticketing system.
